  "prompt": "How do I know viewers of my Facebook profile?",
  "response": "As of my last training cut-off in October 2023, Facebook does not provide a built-in feature that lets users see who has viewed their profile. This is due to privacy policies and concerns. Any app or service claiming to provide this information is likely not legitimate and could be a scam or malware. It's best to avoid these services and protect your personal information.\n\nIf you are interested in understanding engagement with your content, you can see interactions such as likes, comments, and shares on posts, photos, and videos. For public pages (rather than personal profiles), Facebook Insights offers detailed analytics on engagement and audience behavior.\n\nAlways remember to keep your account secure and be cautious of third-party apps or services that request access to your Facebook account.",
